docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:56:- Source extracts for the 2026-07-03_224536 review: `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §11.4 defines `/auth/me/` profile + roles + teams + permissions; its closing implementation rule says React uses `available_actions` for UX while Django remains authoritative. `docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md` §10.6 says UI navigation must be role-aware and backend rejects unauthorized API calls. `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §13.1 includes role codes `it_head`, `internal_auditor`, `management_viewer`, and others that the frontend bridge must handle explicitly or neutrally.
