docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:62:- 002FL completed the frontend lint baseline: `npm run lint` runs `eslint src` with pinned approved packages (`eslint`, `typescript-eslint`, `eslint-plugin-react-hooks`, `eslint-plugin-react-refresh`) and a flat config. The baseline preserves the existing prototype design/permissions and fixes only lint-safe hook dependency, switch-case scope, and `prefer-const` findings. The protected `.ralph/config.yaml` lint gate still needs owner/operator flip to `quality_gates.lint: true`.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:67:- For 002G: build admin user/role management on the existing identity catalogue and `/auth/me/` serialization shape. Use `manage_users` as the explicit permission gate, standard envelopes/pagination, session-bound auth, existing `AuditLog`, and frontend navigation/page guard tests through the 002F shared navigation contract. Do not create free-text roles, teams, or permissions; bind only existing catalogue rows. Suspending a user must revoke active sessions; last-system-admin lock-out should be recorded in `ASSUMPTIONS.md` if source-doc-silent.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:71:- 002G completed admin user-management shell: backend routes under `/api/v1/admin/users/` list/detail users with the `/auth/me/` `roles[{role_code, role_name}]` and `teams[{team_code, team_name}]` shape, bind only existing active `Role`/`Team` rows, set status to `active`/`suspended`, audit role/team/status changes, and revoke active sessions when a user is suspended. Backend gate requires a session-bound active access token plus at least one canonical user-admin permission (`users.user.create`, `users.user.update`, `users.user.disable`); frontend maps those to prototype `manage_users` and adds `admin-users` to `allNavItems`, `PAGE_PERMISSIONS`, and the app route guard. A-014 records the source-silent last active `system_admin` guard: role/status changes that would leave zero active `system_admin` users return `400 VALIDATION_ERROR`.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:72:- For 002H: keep the workflow guard foundation domain-neutral. A shared backend transition guard may define from-state, to-state, required permission, action code, and audit/workflow-event metadata, but must not encode loan eligibility, sanction authority, money amounts, or document-completeness rules. Migrate only the existing tracer transition proof to the shared guard and preserve its public endpoint behavior and `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION` / `403 PERMISSION_DENIED` envelopes.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:74:- 002H completed the shared workflow guard foundation. `sfpcl_credit/workflows/guard.py` defines domain-neutral transition definitions/results plus typed errors for unknown action, missing permission, and invalid state. Tracer services now pass explicit actor permission codes into the shared guard for lifecycle actions while preserving existing tracer URLs, success payloads, `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`, `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION`, audit logs, and workflow events. No schema change.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:75:- Architecture review 2026-07-04_135247 found one corrective follow-up before 002I: 002G's backend admin gate treats any one of `users.user.create`, `users.user.update`, or `users.user.disable` as full user-management authority. Source extract: `auth-permissions.md` §12.1 defines `users.user.read`, `users.user.create`, `users.user.update`, and `users.user.disable` as distinct risk-rated permissions; §15.12 grants System Administrator create/update/disable plus role/config permissions; §19 maps `/settings/users` to `users.user.read`. Corrective slice `002G2` must add action-specific backend permission tests and preserve existing system-admin access.
