 - 002G2 completed the action-aware admin permission gate. `admin_views._authenticated_admin` now takes per-action required permission code sets from `admin_users`: list/detail read needs `users.user.read` OR any write user-admin permission (read fallback per A-015 because seeded `system_admin` lacks `users.user.read`); role assignment and team add/remove need `users.user.update`; suspend needs `users.user.disable`; restore-to-active needs `users.user.update`. `set_status` authorises after parsing the target status (`status_permission_codes`) so suspend and restore are gated differently; check order is `401`→`403`→`400`/`404`, and forbidden partial-permission writes create no `AuditLog` and revoke no session. The now-unused `has_manage_users_permission` helper was removed (`MANAGE_USERS_PERMISSION_CODES` is retained as the read fallback + frontend `manage_users` mapping set). Regression tests cover create-only, update-only, disable-only, and read-only partial roles plus the negative audit/session side effects. No schema change; frontend nav/route unchanged.
 - 002I completed the object-level permission test harness. `sfpcl_credit.identity.modules.object_permissions.evaluate_object_access(...)` is a pure domain-neutral helper that accepts only explicit actor facts (`actor_user_id`, `actor_team_codes`, `actor_permission_codes`) and object facts (`required_permission`, `object_owner_user_id`, `object_team_code`, optional `allow_global`). It returns `ObjectAccessResult(allowed, reason, error_code, required_permission, approval_required)`; missing module permission returns `missing_permission` / `PERMISSION_DENIED`; owner and team matches allow; mismatched or unknown scope returns `owner_mismatch`, `team_mismatch`, or `scope_unknown` with `OBJECT_ACCESS_DENIED`; `scope_unknown` sets `approval_required=True`; explicit `allow_global=True` permits unknown scope only after the required canonical permission is present. Tests verify use with `auth_service.effective_permission_codes(user)`, `User.team_codes()`, and `auth_service.team_payload(user)`. No endpoint, schema change, domain model query, audit row, or frontend change.
 - 002J completed the test-only API contract assertion harness. `sfpcl_credit/tests/api_contracts.py` provides assertions for success envelopes, error envelopes, top-level list pagination, and §44 target `available_actions` item shape. Regression tests cover `/auth/me/` success, admin users pagination, `401 AUTH_REQUIRED`, revoked-session `401 INVALID_TOKEN`, no-permission `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`, create-only partial-admin update denial `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`, and tracer `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION`. No public endpoint, schema change, production import, or frontend change. A-016 records that current `/auth/me/` still returns flat permission-code strings for `available_actions`; the object item shape is asserted only against an internal target-contract sample for future detail endpoints.
